WEBVTT

00:50.051 --> 00:53.452
Cotton tail,
he was runnin' free.

00:53.454 --> 00:55.320
I just chased it
around the hillside,

00:55.322 --> 00:58.524
and then I wait for him
down in the mud.

01:00.561 --> 01:02.227
It was a fast rabbit.

01:02.229 --> 01:04.495
Hmm. Fast, but dumb.

01:04.498 --> 01:06.298
Don't know when
to keep it's head down.

01:11.372 --> 01:14.139
So there it is, rustling
around the leaves, see,

01:16.610 --> 01:19.111
He think, uh, under the
cover of the brush,

01:19.113 --> 01:21.113
them hawks ain't gonna see him.

01:21.115 --> 01:23.749
Tickling the grass...

01:23.751 --> 01:26.485
Then, bam!

01:26.487 --> 01:28.454
A bullet straight to heaven.

01:29.723 --> 01:34.426
Hmm.

01:34.428 --> 01:37.296
Mm, five big ones, little.

01:40.468 --> 01:41.800
Ruth is my friend.

01:43.604 --> 01:46.305
What'd you say?

01:46.307 --> 01:48.774
You're gonna pay
for your sinnin'.

01:50.211 --> 01:54.379
She told me
she wasn't the first.

01:54.381 --> 01:57.716
First?

01:57.718 --> 01:59.718
She can't tell you nothin'.

01:59.720 --> 02:01.120
Who been talkin' them lies?

02:01.122 --> 02:02.421
Your preacher?

02:10.798 --> 02:13.432
Angels.

02:18.606 --> 02:20.339
Get her, boy.

02:22.476 --> 02:23.842
Rabbit's running.

02:34.388 --> 02:38.590
Go ahead now,
there ain't nowhere safe.

02:38.592 --> 02:41.426
Hawk is gonna find you.

02:57.745 --> 02:59.178
♪ You caught me smiling ♪

02:59.180 --> 03:02.881
♪ why'd you wait so long? ♪

03:04.552 --> 03:06.652
♪ It's just
my only crutch ♪

03:06.654 --> 03:09.454
♪ and it's over
my shoulder ♪

03:09.456 --> 03:12.791
♪ well, you're
talking so fast ♪

03:12.793 --> 03:16.662
♪ that the days
turned out slower ♪

03:16.664 --> 03:18.630
♪ ooh ♪

03:20.234 --> 03:23.502
♪ keep on the path
I sent you on ♪

03:26.941 --> 03:31.977
♪ those visionaries
aren't 'round no more ♪

03:34.381 --> 03:38.850
♪ they left their markings
in the coconut forest ♪

03:38.852 --> 03:42.554
♪ and scraped
on the shore ♪

03:42.556 --> 03:46.825
♪ for the days
that had rolled on ♪

03:49.697 --> 03:54.266
♪ keep on the path
I sent you on ♪

03:55.369 --> 03:57.502
♪ I sent you on ♪

04:12.553 --> 04:17.456
♪ another quiet day
has passed me by ♪

04:19.392 --> 04:21.994
♪ and every
now and then ♪

04:21.995 --> 04:24.696
♪ the silence is broken ♪

04:24.698 --> 04:28.367
♪ well, I heard it
so sharp ♪

04:28.369 --> 04:32.004
♪ but I had to
just go on ♪

04:32.006 --> 04:34.906
♪ go on ♪

04:34.908 --> 04:38.744
♪ keep on the path
I sent you on ♪

04:50.891 --> 04:52.591
Hmm.

05:42.810 --> 05:45.711
Hi, there.

05:45.713 --> 05:48.814
I reckon you ran
up front side of a nail.

05:48.816 --> 05:50.982
Yeah, I think so.

05:50.984 --> 05:52.918
I tried calling for help, but...

05:52.920 --> 05:55.020
Yeah, that wouldn't work
when you need it to,

05:55.022 --> 05:56.088
now would it?

05:56.090 --> 05:58.523
No, I guess not.

05:58.525 --> 05:59.658
Well, let me have a little look,

05:59.660 --> 06:01.393
take a see what you've got here.

06:01.395 --> 06:03.128
Thank you.

06:04.098 --> 06:05.397
Well, yep.

06:05.399 --> 06:06.431
It's on there.

06:06.433 --> 06:08.533
Yeah, I did my best.

06:11.772 --> 06:14.406
Y'all them folk
what moved up to Caperwood.

06:14.408 --> 06:16.041
Yeah, we are.

06:17.111 --> 06:19.611
It's a good old house.

06:19.613 --> 06:22.114
Good old house.

06:22.116 --> 06:24.015
Yeah, it is.

06:25.519 --> 06:27.486
Far cry from the city, huh?

06:29.656 --> 06:32.090
Yeah, it's beautiful.

06:32.092 --> 06:34.826
Well, along with our
pristine roads,

06:34.828 --> 06:37.429
people say we famous
for our views.

06:37.431 --> 06:38.797
Thank you so much.

06:38.799 --> 06:40.432
- What do I owe you?
- No, ma'am.

06:40.434 --> 06:43.034
No, I could not have
done this myself.

06:43.036 --> 06:44.703
Ah.

06:44.705 --> 06:45.704
You could've.

06:45.706 --> 06:47.172
And you would have too.

06:47.174 --> 06:48.874
Besides, I'd hate to
have to haul you in

06:48.876 --> 06:50.442
for bribing an officer
of the law

06:50.444 --> 06:51.777
before you all even get settled.

06:51.779 --> 06:54.713
Okay.

06:54.715 --> 06:57.182
Thank you again.

06:57.184 --> 07:00.685
Ma'am, excuse me.
What is that right there?

07:00.687 --> 07:03.021
It's a birthmark.

07:04.558 --> 07:06.792
Good day.

07:08.829 --> 07:11.196
Oh, ma'am?

07:11.198 --> 07:12.931
One thing I might should say,

07:12.933 --> 07:15.467
being as y'all
ain't from around here,

07:15.469 --> 07:17.769
not all places fit for visit.

07:18.972 --> 07:20.639
What do you mean?

07:20.641 --> 07:24.042
Well, there's some strange
folk around here.

07:24.044 --> 07:26.044
They made their life on
their own, god bless them,

07:26.046 --> 07:28.079
and they not
be disturbed, is all.

07:49.837 --> 07:52.003
Wh... ah!

08:02.015 --> 08:03.548
Hey, babe.

08:03.550 --> 08:04.983
Hey, sweetie.

08:04.985 --> 08:06.218
Where you been?

08:06.220 --> 08:07.853
Oh, don't ask.

08:07.855 --> 08:08.920
Had a little bit of a disaster.

08:08.922 --> 08:10.555
Hi.

08:10.557 --> 08:12.090
- Mmm.
- I missed you.

08:12.092 --> 08:14.659
Aw. I missed you too.

08:14.661 --> 08:16.995
I blew a tire though, that's
why I'm late. I'm sorry.

08:16.997 --> 08:19.030
Ah, please tell me
you didn't change it.

08:19.032 --> 08:21.600
No.
I actually tried to,

08:21.602 --> 08:22.601
but then a local
came by and helped me.

08:22.603 --> 08:23.802
Oh, wow.

08:23.804 --> 08:25.737
He was a little creepy,
he still did it.

08:25.739 --> 08:27.239
Yeah, and I almost
cut off my finger.

08:27.241 --> 08:28.540
You almost cut off your finger?

08:28.542 --> 08:29.641
Yeah, perils of house work.

08:29.643 --> 08:31.610
Oh, look at you, tough guy.

08:31.612 --> 08:32.611
Yeah, watch out.

08:32.613 --> 08:33.778
Your nails getting dirty.

08:33.780 --> 08:35.013
- Right?
- I like it.

08:35.015 --> 08:37.982
So, uh, what are
you making tonight?

08:37.985 --> 08:40.051
Uh, I was gonna
make something called,

08:40.053 --> 08:42.020
"my husband's making
dinner for me."

08:48.896 --> 08:50.061
Job well done today.

08:50.063 --> 08:51.997
Yeah, thanks.

08:51.999 --> 08:55.901
We're like, 20% done.

08:55.903 --> 08:57.903
I think we're finally
where we need to be.

08:57.905 --> 08:59.905
This really feels like home.

08:59.907 --> 09:01.873
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

09:24.998 --> 09:26.631
Ah!

09:26.633 --> 09:28.300
Hi!

09:28.302 --> 09:30.035
Oh, it's so good to see you.

09:30.037 --> 09:31.269
Great to see you.
This is Dave.

09:31.271 --> 09:33.171
Hi, Dave.
Sarah.

09:33.173 --> 09:34.739
- Congratulations.
- Thank you so much.

09:34.741 --> 09:36.675
Thank you for coming.
This is my husband.

09:36.677 --> 09:37.676
- Matt.
- How are you doing? Dave.

09:37.678 --> 09:39.110
Yeah, pleasure.

09:39.112 --> 09:40.712
- You...
- I know, I'm huge.

09:40.714 --> 09:42.614
I'm huge.

09:42.616 --> 09:44.649
Come here, come on,
I wanna show you.

09:44.651 --> 09:47.018
Oh my god, I'm so jealous.

09:47.020 --> 09:48.887
Oh, don't be, please.

09:48.889 --> 09:50.722
It's yours anytime.
You just say the word.

09:50.724 --> 09:52.591
Well, it's actually the bank's.

09:52.593 --> 09:54.893
But, lest let facts get in the way.

09:54.895 --> 09:55.961
And this one too, of course,

09:55.963 --> 09:56.962
if he plays his cards right.

09:56.964 --> 09:57.963
Oh, okay.

09:57.965 --> 09:59.631
No pressure.

09:59.633 --> 10:02.934
So... this is where
we're gonna do it.

10:02.936 --> 10:04.302
Uh... do it?

10:04.304 --> 10:06.037
Yeah, that's where
the magic happens.

10:06.039 --> 10:07.973
Yeah, we've already
got the midwife,

10:07.975 --> 10:10.809
and of course, my favorite
doctor is going to be on-call.

10:10.811 --> 10:13.178
Oh, so you're giving birth here?

10:13.180 --> 10:14.746
That's the plan,
fingers crossed.

10:14.748 --> 10:17.716
You guys, this
is really wonderful

10:17.718 --> 10:19.351
I'm... I'm really
excited for you guys.

10:19.353 --> 10:22.087
Thank you.
We're pretty happy.

10:22.089 --> 10:24.089
Okay, I wanna show you the
rest of the house. Come here.

10:24.091 --> 10:26.057
- Excuse us.
- Thank you.

10:26.059 --> 10:27.292
You, sir?
Thirsty?

10:27.294 --> 10:28.994
Absolutely.

10:28.996 --> 10:31.229
Oh, he's really cute.

10:31.231 --> 10:35.033
My god. Yeah,
yeah, well done.

10:35.035 --> 10:38.003
So, any tips for a new local?

10:38.005 --> 10:39.838
Oh, uh, soda's fine.

10:39.840 --> 10:40.972
Okay.

10:40.974 --> 10:43.174
Uh, sorry, tips for a local?

10:43.176 --> 10:45.043
Yeah, Sarah says
you grew up around here.

10:45.045 --> 10:47.245
Oh, more like 50 miles
south, closer to the city.

10:47.247 --> 10:50.115
Oh, yeah, it's a different
world out here.

10:50.117 --> 10:52.217
Yeah, it's interesting.

10:53.887 --> 10:55.186
I hear you play football.

10:55.188 --> 10:57.389
Used to. Had a ride
back at state,

10:57.391 --> 10:58.957
till I threw my back out.

10:58.959 --> 11:00.291
Oh, I'm sorry
to hear about that.

11:00.293 --> 11:02.060
- And now?
- Personal trainer.

11:02.062 --> 11:03.061
Play a little touch
on the weekends,

11:03.063 --> 11:04.663
if I'm feeling frisky.

11:04.665 --> 11:07.098
Oh, nice. Yeah,
back trauma's no joke.

11:07.100 --> 11:09.768
And the list gets scarier
with football players.

11:09.770 --> 11:11.302
Count your blessings.

11:11.304 --> 11:13.371
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

11:13.373 --> 11:16.174
So, how long has it been
since you've seen them, then?

11:16.176 --> 11:17.876
Every other month or so, maybe.

11:17.878 --> 11:19.711
- I don't know.
- That's great.

11:19.713 --> 11:21.913
That means this medicine's
actually working then.

11:21.915 --> 11:25.116
Yeah, I mean I'm not... I'm not
gonna embarrass you, or anything,

11:25.118 --> 11:26.885
if that's what
you're worried about.

11:26.887 --> 11:29.354
No. That is not... you have
never embarrassed me.

11:29.356 --> 11:31.389
- That's not what I meant at all.
- I know.

11:31.391 --> 11:33.091
You know, I've had my own
issues with seeing things.

11:33.093 --> 11:37.162
I know, I know.
It's just... it's just weird.

11:37.164 --> 11:38.963
You live with these people
since you're a kid,

11:38.965 --> 11:41.099
and then, a doctor comes along,

11:41.101 --> 11:42.400
and tells you
that they're not real.

11:42.402 --> 11:43.702
That it doesn't exist,

11:43.704 --> 11:45.070
and to take this medicine,

11:45.072 --> 11:46.304
and it's gonna make
you all better.

11:46.306 --> 11:50.041
And... and then
everyone's gone.

11:50.043 --> 11:52.243
I'm not gone.
I'm not going anywhere.

11:52.245 --> 11:53.912
Matt's not going anywhere.

11:53.914 --> 11:55.313
Dave seems pretty real.

11:55.315 --> 11:59.050
I mean, that guy...
Wow, he seems really real.

11:59.052 --> 12:00.885
I think I really like him.

12:00.887 --> 12:03.007
Good, I'm really looking
forward to getting to know...

12:07.494 --> 12:09.761
No fucking way.

12:09.763 --> 12:11.863
Whoo! Nice digs!

12:15.836 --> 12:17.969
This place is sick.

12:17.971 --> 12:19.170
Hey.

12:19.172 --> 12:21.406
What the hell, stranger?

12:21.408 --> 12:23.374
Ah, you know,
I figured you invited us,

12:23.376 --> 12:25.043
and what kind of
uncle would I be

12:25.045 --> 12:26.478
if I didn't show up?

12:26.480 --> 12:28.413
Hi.

12:28.415 --> 12:31.249
I did invite you. That was
about five months ago though,

12:31.251 --> 12:32.917
and you were supposed to RSVP.

12:32.919 --> 12:34.953
Well, if RSVP means show up
with dirty laundry,

12:34.955 --> 12:36.955
then we did just that.

12:36.957 --> 12:38.757
- That's exactly what it means.
- Yeah.

12:38.759 --> 12:40.525
Hey, I want you to meet
the Pearl of my life.

12:40.527 --> 12:42.494
This is Skye. Skye,
this is my sister, Sarah.

12:42.496 --> 12:44.996
- Hey, god you are gorgeous.
- Oh, thank you.

12:44.998 --> 12:46.765
Dude, thank you
for letting us crash.

12:46.767 --> 12:49.134
- So cool of you.
- You are so welcome.

12:49.136 --> 12:52.437
And this right here
is Sabrina the teenage Bruja.

12:52.439 --> 12:53.872
All grown up.

12:53.874 --> 12:55.106
Hey, it looks like
you've come a long way.

12:55.108 --> 12:56.274
Hi, thank you very much.

12:56.276 --> 12:57.842
Yeah, that is ours right there.

12:57.844 --> 12:58.843
- We love her. Don't we?
- Mm-hmm.

12:58.845 --> 13:00.044
You own it, huh?

13:00.046 --> 13:01.346
Is that doctor Matt over there?

13:01.348 --> 13:02.480
Hey, we're gonna go
get cleaned up

13:02.482 --> 13:04.215
real quick, all right?

13:04.217 --> 13:05.884
What's for lunch, bud?

13:07.554 --> 13:09.854
You don't have to worry
about embarrassing me now,

13:09.856 --> 13:11.956
because my brother's here.

13:13.894 --> 13:15.360
Hi.

13:19.399 --> 13:21.132
Hey, hey...
White wine?

13:21.134 --> 13:22.867
Oh, no, this is apple juice.

13:22.869 --> 13:26.204
I just like to pretend.

13:26.206 --> 13:27.472
Oh, rad.
What kind of clothes?

13:27.474 --> 13:29.007
Uh, casual work wear,

13:29.009 --> 13:30.575
that's what I call it anyway.

13:30.577 --> 13:32.377
It's like, light wools
and stitched patterns.

13:32.379 --> 13:36.514
- Cool. Like um, this?
- Yeah, like this, actually.

13:36.516 --> 13:38.349
Nice, I like it.

13:38.351 --> 13:41.219
So, you really think
I'd enjoy burning man?

13:41.221 --> 13:44.422
Bro, would you enjoy

13:44.424 --> 13:47.325
the true freedom of the mind?

13:47.327 --> 13:48.560
Yeah, it's a good little clinic.

13:48.562 --> 13:50.461
Only about 20 intakes a day.

13:50.463 --> 13:52.063
Well, that'll be a change.

13:52.065 --> 13:53.565
Yeah, I can't wait.

13:53.567 --> 13:55.333
See the life's good
good for your 20s,

13:55.335 --> 13:57.135
but after it gets
a little crazy.

13:57.137 --> 13:59.437
Well, it's perfect for you guys.

13:59.439 --> 14:01.372
Yeah, we've been just like, traveling
around for the last six months.

14:01.374 --> 14:03.508
Yeah, Eric said
like Oregon, Arizona.

14:03.510 --> 14:05.043
Oh, Arizona was amazing.

14:05.045 --> 14:07.312
The red rocks are so groovy.

14:07.314 --> 14:10.114
We're trying to get down to the golf
coast for summer. Those cute towns.

14:10.116 --> 14:11.950
- Cute towns.
- Yes, those cute towns.

14:11.952 --> 14:14.352
- I wanna see them.
- So cute.

14:14.354 --> 14:16.187
- Oh, I like your charm.
- Oh, right on, yeah.

14:16.189 --> 14:18.056
I got this at this
little flea market

14:18.058 --> 14:19.557
in Tahoma, you know?

14:19.559 --> 14:21.960
And it kinda like...

14:21.962 --> 14:24.429
Well, it kinda drew us
here, you know?

14:24.431 --> 14:26.531
Have you been out
to the woods yet?

14:26.533 --> 14:30.101
Oh, no, we haven't had time yet.

14:30.103 --> 14:31.703
Does the doctor
not want to pitch a tent?

14:32.606 --> 14:34.505
Do you guys need anything?

14:34.507 --> 14:35.573
- No, I'm good, baby.
- All right.

14:35.575 --> 14:37.141
I'm good, thank you.

14:38.612 --> 14:40.478
- How great is she?
- Yeah.

14:40.480 --> 14:41.880
Yeah, she seems really sweet.

14:41.882 --> 14:43.114
She is.

14:43.116 --> 14:46.050
When are you planning
on getting home?

14:46.052 --> 14:49.420
Well, this is it.

14:49.422 --> 14:52.223
Oh, come on, don't... don't
give me that look. All right?

14:52.225 --> 14:54.125
I'm not trying to move
into your big house

14:54.127 --> 14:55.560
with too many rooms.

14:55.562 --> 14:57.562
Our home is this slab
that we rolled in on.

14:57.564 --> 14:59.330
That's our home now.

14:59.332 --> 15:03.034
- You're gonna live in the Van?
- Yeah.

15:03.036 --> 15:06.137
Yeah, I mean, besides,
we can't really, um,

15:06.139 --> 15:07.939
we can't really go back
to the apartment, you know,

15:07.941 --> 15:10.074
we haven't paid rent
since like, November.

15:10.076 --> 15:12.243
But, no, but... the walls
were getting small,

15:12.245 --> 15:14.379
- and it was... it was really
like... -Jesus, Eric.

15:14.381 --> 15:15.914
I don't know,
the energy wasn't there.

15:15.916 --> 15:17.115
- You know?
- Okay.

15:17.117 --> 15:18.616
Have you thought
about getting a job?

15:18.618 --> 15:21.119
Yeah. Yeah, I mean...

15:21.121 --> 15:22.687
I don't know, you know,

15:22.689 --> 15:24.522
it's like...
Life is about living,

15:24.524 --> 15:26.491
you know? Living.

15:26.493 --> 15:29.627
Yeah, living takes money, Eric.

15:29.629 --> 15:31.462
Food, gas.

15:31.464 --> 15:34.565
We'll be all right.
I always am, you know that.

15:34.567 --> 15:36.200
Ahem.

15:36.202 --> 15:37.936
Look at you, grill master.

15:37.938 --> 15:39.637
Yeah, it's actually all local.

15:39.639 --> 15:41.172
- Yeah? Cool.
- Yeah.

15:41.174 --> 15:44.175
- Would you like one?
- Uh,

15:44.177 --> 15:45.710
- I'm actually a veg.
- You're a veg.

15:45.712 --> 15:47.378
- Yeah. -Damn, I wish
I would have known.

15:47.380 --> 15:48.947
- No, dude, it's cool.
- No, hold tight.

15:48.949 --> 15:51.449
Um, I think I might
have something for you.

15:51.451 --> 15:52.951
Don't like go out of your
way for me, or anything.

15:52.953 --> 15:54.485
Not a problem.

15:54.487 --> 15:55.653
I hope that that's enough

15:55.655 --> 15:57.221
to carry you for a little bit.

15:57.223 --> 15:58.323
Oh, babe, it's more than enough.

15:58.325 --> 16:00.091
Thank you.

16:00.093 --> 16:02.427
Babe, do you have
any of that pasta left?

16:02.429 --> 16:03.995
Hey, you need a beer,
or something?

16:03.997 --> 16:08.366
- Uh, I'm good.
- All right.

16:09.502 --> 16:11.035
Really?

16:12.339 --> 16:14.205
What am I supposed to do?

16:23.750 --> 16:26.284
This is such
a quaint little spread.

16:26.286 --> 16:28.019
Who would have thought
that big city elitism

16:28.021 --> 16:29.654
would travel so cool
to the country, huh?

16:29.656 --> 16:31.456
Yeah, well,
that big city elitism

16:31.458 --> 16:34.525
is financing your dirtbag life.

16:34.527 --> 16:37.495
Hey, so, uh, Matt, I see you
still got dad's old Jeep.

16:37.497 --> 16:39.364
Yeah, it's a work horse.

16:39.366 --> 16:42.100
Hauled some brush off the
road with it last weekend.

16:42.102 --> 16:44.202
I always thought that
doctor's all drove Audis.

16:44.204 --> 16:47.405
- You know?
- Well, this doctor doesn't.

16:47.407 --> 16:49.307
But that's just because
he's made some sacrifices

16:49.309 --> 16:51.242
for me and our family.

16:51.244 --> 16:53.478
The baby is the only thing
that matters to us.

